Right, I completely see how that would prevent it from qualifying as a tail call, my misunderstanding was still different though. For some reason I thought that even if the recursive function was defined within the try-catch block (as below) it would prevent it from using a tail call:<p><pre><code>  try
    let rec func ... =
      ...
      func( ... )

    let result = func( ... )
  with
  | ex -> ...
</code></pre>
I don't know exactly how I ended up thinking that, seems a bit silly in retrospect.
